<paragraph id="A6207D7FB91BFF30FF7C2AC23424FE5D" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="121">Dorsal fin with i, 6 (3) rays; fin margin convex, located halfway between snout tip and adipose fin origin. Dorsal-fin spine strong, gently curved, with 5–6 serrae, longer than depth of body. Adipose fin shallow, acutely incised at the posterior extremity of its base with elongated posterior pointed tip (fig. 3). Pectoral fin with i,9 (2) or 10 rays; posterior fin margin almost straight. Pectoral spine very broad, covered with thick skin, its posterior margin with 12–13 serrae. Pelvic fin with i,5 (3) rays, its posterior margin slightly convex, surpasses the vent, tip of adpressed fin not reaching anal-fin origin. Anal fin with iv, 8 or 9 (2) rays, almost straight posterior margin. Caudal fin with 7+8 branched rays, strongly forked, with lower lobe slightly longer than upper lobe.</paragraph>
