<subSubSection id="EE852EF4B91BFF30FF7C2CBA32E1F8F9" pageId="3" pageNumber="121" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A6207D7FB91BFF30FF7C2CBA32E1F8F9" blockId="3.[151,1436,1595,1874]" pageId="3" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis id="94EBA16DB91BFF30FF7C2CBA3101F8DD" bold="true" box="[199,353,1775,1801]" pageId="3" pageNumber="121">Distribution.</emphasis>
The species is presently known only from the 
<typeStatus id="7924C3DDB91BFF30FCD32CA533F8F8DE" box="[872,920,1776,1802]" pageId="3" pageNumber="121">type</typeStatus>
locality, the Yu River, a tributary of Chindwin River, 
<collectingRegion id="645BB39DB91BFF30FF592D46315CF8F9" box="[226,316,1811,1837]" country="Myanmar" name="Sagaing" pageId="3" pageNumber="121">Sagaing</collectingRegion>
Division, 
<collectingCountry id="DE883DEFB91BFF30FE092D41327FF8FA" box="[434,543,1812,1838]" name="Myanmar" pageId="3" pageNumber="121">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="3EA461FAB91BFF30FD952D463213F8F9" box="[558,627,1811,1837]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1113,1137]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,184,1087]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1436,181,1090]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Map showing type locality of Glyptothorax yuensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488293" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488293/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="121">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EE852EF4B91BFF30FF7C2D6233C7F885" box="[199,935,1847,1874]" pageId="3" pageNumber="121" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="A6207D7FB91BFF30FF7C2D6233C7F885" blockId="3.[151,1436,1595,1874]" box="[199,935,1847,1874]" pageId="3" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis id="94EBA16DB91BFF30FF7C2D62312EF885" bold="true" box="[199,334,1847,1873]" pageId="3" pageNumber="121">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after its 
<typeStatus id="7924C3DDB91BFF30FD1D2D6D32B6F886" box="[678,726,1848,1874]" pageId="3" pageNumber="121">type</typeStatus>
locality, Yu River.
</paragraph>
